the artistic production of the Comitán Valley from that of other Maya locales. After the Maya abandoned their powerful lowland centers, those in Comitán were maintained, a distinction from which Earley draws new insights concerning the Maya collapse. Richly illustrated with never-before-published photographs of sculptures unearthed from key archaeological sites, The Comitán Valley is an illuminating work of art historical recovery and interpretation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aMaya sculpturexSocial aspectszMexicozChiapas2DLC. 0aMaya sculpturexSocial aspectszMexicozChiapas. 0aMaya sculpturezMexicozChiapas2DLC. 0aMaya sculpturezMexicozChiapas. 0aStele (Archaeology)xSocial aspectszMexicozChiapas2DLC. 0aStele (Archaeology)xSocial aspectszMexicozChiapas. 0aStele (Archaeology)zMexicozChiapas2DLC. 0aStele (Archaeology)zMexicozChiapas. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  aArt history, archaeology, anthropology, history, Maya, Indigenous, Latin America, Mexico, sculpture, architecture, cave art, iconography, frontier, innovation, identity, ballgame, religion, political history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Texas Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079782440uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/32712840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477327135423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477327135/original  a978-3-11-079782-